organic_results.title: Cultural consumption and the educational plans of Australian secondary school students
organic_results.snippet: This article assesses the impact of cultural consumption on the educational aspirations of Australian secondary school students, taking into account other factors, such as the students' social origin and the type of school they attend. The analysis indicates that cultural consumption is a significant source of differentiation among boys' plans to obtain a higher education but has less of an impact on girls' plans.
